ft.and.bubble.right.fill","roleId":"chat","colorToken":"accent","kind":"interface"},"detail":"git log --oneline -15","label":"run_command","status":"succeeded","kind":"toolCall","id":"act-91"},{"speaker":{"displayName":"Foreman","icon":"point.3.connected.trianglepath.dotted","roleId":"foreman","colorToken":"graphite","kind":"system"},"detail":"allow run_command","label":"Operator gate","status":"succeeded","kind":"systemMarker","id":"act-92"},{"speaker":{"displayName":"Chat Agent","icon":"bubble.left.and.bubble.right.fill","roleId":"chat","colorToken":"accent","kind":"interface"},"detail":"I have a strong picture from the README, FEATURES.md, and git history. Here's the draft:\n\n---\n\n## `docs\/VISION.md`\n\n**Purpose:** Code trust, with an expiration date. Certify makes code quality a continuous process — not a one-time gate — by evaluating every code unit against versioned policies and issuing time-bound certifications that expire by design.\n\n**Principles:**\n- **Time-bound trust** — certifications expire; trust must be renewed\n- **Evidence-driven** — deterministic checks are authoritative; AI review supplements, never overrides\n- **Repository-native** — runs locally and in CI; no centralized control plane required\n- **Language-agnostic** — polyglot support with a generic fallback for any language\n- **Incremental adoption** — advisory mode first, scope to changed code, expand over time\n- **Transparent governance** — overrides require rationale; every action is auditable\n- **Policy-as-code** — versioned, reviewable, stored in the repo alongside the code\n\n**Non-Goals:**\n- Not a static analysis tool — Certify integrates analyzers into a certification framework\n- Not a CI\/CD system — it evaluates trustworthiness, not build\/deploy status\n- Not a centralized SaaS — operates offline via CLI and GitHub Actions\n- Not a replacement for human code review — scores objective dimensions, not design taste\n- Not a security scanner — security is one of nine quality dimensions, not the sole focus\n\n**Success Criteria:**\n- Teams can identify which code is trusted, expired, or decertified at a glance\n- Teams can trace every certification to the policy version that produced it\n- Technical debt is prioritized through evidence and trust decay, not intuition\n- Adoption is incremental without overwhelming noise on first run\n- Architecture supports new language adapters without core redesign\n\n---","label":"Thinking","status":"succeeded","kind":"thinking","id":"act-95"},{"speaker":{"displayName":"Chat Agent","icon":"bubble.left.and.bubble.right.fill","roleId":"chat","colorToken":"accent","kind":"interface"},"detail":"Write this as docs\/VISION.md?","label":"ask_user","status":"succeeded","kind":"toolCall","id":"act-96"},{"speaker":{"displayName":"Foreman","icon":"point.3.connected.trianglepath.dotted","roleId":"foreman","colorToken":"graphite","kind":"system"},"detail":"allow ask_user","label":"Operator gate","status":"succeeded","kind":"systemMarker","id":"act-97"},{"speaker":{"displayName":"Chat Agent","icon":"bubble.left.and.bubble.right.fill","roleId":"chat","colorToken":"accent","kind":"interface"},"detail":"docs\/VISION.md","label":"write_file","status":"succeeded","kind":"toolCall","id":"act-100"},{"speaker":{"displayName":"Foreman","icon":"point.3.connected.trianglepath.dotted","roleId":"foreman","colorToken":"graphite","kind":"system"},"detail":"allow write_file","label":"Operator gate","status":"succeeded","kind":"systemMarker","id":"act-101"},{"speaker":{"displayName":"Chat Agent","icon":"bubble.left.and.bubble.right.fill","roleId":"chat","colorToken":"accent","kind":"interface"},"detail":"Now add VISION.md to the project config and commit.","label":"Thinking","status":"succeeded","kind":"thinking","id":"act-104"},{"speaker":{"displayName":"Chat Agent","icon":"bubble.left.and.bubble.right.fill","roleId":"chat","colorToken":"accent","kind":"interface"},"detail":"iksnae\/code-certification","label":"configure_projec